Would you mind to elaborate (give an example)?<p>I&#x27;ve toyed with bonjour spoofing before, but I always found querying was <i>incredibly</i> difficult, using <i>dns-sd</i>, e.g.:<p><pre><code>   HOST=`(dns-sd -L &quot;Name of Machine&quot; _http._tcp local
   | grep -o &quot;at .* (interface&quot;
   | grep -o &quot;[a-zA-Z\-]\{1,\}\.local&quot; &
   ); sleep 1 && pkill -f dns-sq`
</code></pre>
Obviously tailored specifically for that project, but I hope you catch my drift. And add to that the port lookup.<p>I&#x27;m fairly certain I&#x27;m not using it as you do, so would you mind giving an example of how your use MDNS for local dev testing?
